*[ProMe](https://prome.games)* (pronounced “pro-may”) is a companion for *The Protector’s Memories*, a solo <abbr title="Table-Top Role Playing Game">TTRPG</abbr> by Enzo Salviato. It started as a small tool for rolling and recording <abbr title="Non-Playable Characters">NPCs</abbr> and grew into a full progressive web app: offline-friendly play, optional ambient audio, and a strong focus on atmosphere and clarity.

{% callout "warning" %}
ProMe is not a digital edition of the game: you still need to own the official rulebook. The app supports pen-and-paper play with structured notes, maps, and helpers.
{% endcallout %}

## What it offers

- A character sheet to track progress, stats, resources, inventory, and more.
- An interactive and customizable map, with per-biome theming and a hexagonal grid.
- Generators to automatically build characters and villages according to the game rules.
- Complete offline support, with local storage and optional cloud sync.
- Ambient audio soundtracks, with cross-fading between biomes, and ambient-only variants.

